title: Roads, Maya Forest, Guatemala-Belize, 2000
creator: UCSB Maya Forest GIS
note_description: In the 2000 field season of the BRASS/El Pilar Program, the UCSB Maya Forest GIS collected and processed GPS data for drivable roads in parts of Western Belize and the Peten of Guatemala. Selected for the work were Garmin GPS units accurate from 3-10m (after the US government released Selective Availability SA of error).
rights_note: Please acknowledge the UCSB Maya Forest GIS, in any derived data products, reports or publications.

title: Archeological Sites, Maya Forest, Guatemala-Belize-Mexico, 1995
creator: University of Florida. GeoPlan Center
note_description: This is a digital database of the Maya Forest Region of Mexico, Guatemala, and Belize. Coverages presented here are ArcView Shape files. The projection is UTM Zone 16, using the NAD 1927 datum and the Clarke 1866 spheroid. This coverage contains point locations and names for 530 archaeological sites identified from various sources for the project area.
rights_note: Please acknowledge the University of Florida, the Paseo Pantera Consortium, and the US Agency for International Development in any derived data product, reports or publications
